        <subsection xml:id="AntecedentsAndConsequents">
            <title>Antecedents and Consequents</title>
            <p>In a period, the phrase ending with the less conclusive cadence is called the <q><term>antecedent</term></q><idx><h>antecedent</h><h>definition of</h></idx> and the phrase ending with the more conclusive cadence is called the <q><term>consequent</term><idx><h>consequent</h><h>definition of</h></idx>.</q> These can be thought of as being in a <q>question and answer</q> relationship.</p>
