    <section xml:id="PhraseGroupsAndPhraseChains">
        <title>Phrase Groups and Phrase Chains</title>
        <p>Phrase groups and phrase chains are not periods. In phrase groups and phrase chains, <em>the final cadence is a half cadence</em>. A <term>phrase group</term><idx><h>phrase group</h><h>definition of</h></idx> consists of at least two phrases whose melodies begin similarly and has the final phrase ending in a half cadence. The terminology in this section draws from Douglass Green’s <pubtitle>Form in Tonal Music</pubtitle>.</p>
        <figure>
            <caption>Couperin, 5 Pi&#x00E8;ces de Clavecin, 4. Le Petit-Rien (Ordre XIV, 8)</caption>
            <idx><h>Couperin</h><h>5 Pi&#x00E8;ces de Clavecin, 4. Le Petit-Rien (Ordre XIV, 8) (phrase group)</h></idx>
